    "Catalogue/collection listing": "No",
    "Link to online catalogue/finding aid": "",
    "Outputs created by collection holder": "",
    "Any other information": "Oral history was a particular interest of mine and I also have some selected interviews with friends and family. However the series for Mordialloc Primary's 125th Celebration is an important historical collection with\nperspectives from students, parents, cleaners, teachers ,and principals with the World Wars and Depression mentioned, polio epidemic, transition from horse to car, encounters with Pharlap (Mordialloc Primary had special dispensation to keep students to 14 years of age because those wanting to be jockeys did not intend going to high school.) At the time Mordialloc Primary was under threat of closure by the Kennett Government, I was told anything I did had to be 'cost negative' therefore I paid for all the cassettes, photographs, developing and photocopying etc."
