    "Collection description": "Our oral history collection is in three parts:\n1. A set of approximately 30 audio cassette tapes, which are recordings of interviews and informal discussions conducted with Linton residents or former residents during the 1980s and early 1990s.\n2. A set of approximately 17 CD recordings of interviews with Linton residents or former residents, conducted as part of PhD research undertaken by LDHS President Jill Wheeler, in 2005 and 2006. Jill donated these recordings to the Historical Society after she completed her research.\n3. Approximately 12 audio-visual recordings on DVDs. These are recordings of talks given at LDHS 'History Nights' between 2012 and 2022. Speakers were all Linton residents or former residents, who outlined their particular family's history in Linton township and district, and recalled aspects of life in Linton as they were growing up.",
