    "Outputs created by collection holder": "",
    "Any other information": "My intention has been to write an article about the programme with discussion about some of the more memorable interviews and segments. I am unsure of how or if copyright is relevant as all the programmes are live broadcasts. Programmes were put together quickly each week and as this was live radio it captures a style of presentation that is lost when something is pre-recorded or presented as a podcast – or when one of the presenters is also not the show's producer. We had a deliberate focus to make the segments widely accessible and we often cited the old adage about radio being the theatre of the mind so we tried to avoid the style of broadcast that was a lecture on the radio."
