    "Focus on first nations": "No",
    "Collection places": "Rural Australia",
    "Collection description": "You Tube video clips featuring Percy Leason's cartoons offering a snapshot of life in the 1920s - 1960s, capturing the spirit of rural Australian utilising Kaniva's main street, social life and local characters.",
    "Collection purpose": "The Wiregrass Heritage Trail aims to shine a light on the social history of rural Australia through the lens of Percy Leason's cartoons. Percy Leason, born in 1889, and in 1924 became Australia's highest-paid cartoonist. His Wiregrass series, based on the mythical town of Wiregrass, captured the essence of rural life in Australia during the twenties and thirties. This project aims to use his cartoons and story telling to engage with new audiences through a main street trail with people who may not necessarily engage with traditional art galleries and museums. NB This is a work in progress and I am still capturing stories. I hope to be finished by the end of the year, but I am trying to fit this around many other jobs and daily life.",
